canonical:
  title: 趙浚政丞眞贊
  author: 鄭道傳
  language: lzh
  text: 於惟我后迺有重臣重臣伊誰趙公維賢志存經濟拯世之屯手扶日轂昇于中天功在王室澤被生民雖古名相莫能或先惟公之心惟公之眞與國匹休於千萬年
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 趙浚政丞眞贊
  author: 鄭道傳
  language: lzh
  text: 於惟我后。迺有重臣。重臣伊誰。趙公維賢。志存經濟。拯世之屯。手扶日轂。昇于中天。功在王室。澤被生民。雖古名相。莫能或先。惟公之心。惟公之眞。與國匹休。於千萬年。
korean:
  title: 조준정승 진찬
  author: 정도전
  language: kor
  text: 아아, 우리 임금게서는 마침내 소중한 신하를 두시었다. 소중한 신하란 그 누구인가. 조공(趙公)이 오직 착하였도다. 정치에 뜻을 두어 시국의 어려움을 구제하였고 몸으로 임금을 받들어 높은 자리에 오르게 하였다. 공적은 왕실(王室)에 남아 있으며 덕택은 백성에 흘러 내렸다. 옛날에 유명한 대사인들 공보다 더 훌륭한 인물이 누구 있는가. 오직 공의 마음이 공의 얼굴로 나라와 함께 영화를 같이하라. 천만 년에 이르기까지.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0540_010_0360&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Eulogy for Prime Minister Zhao Jun
  author: Jeong Do-jeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Behold, our sovereign has at last secured a minister of true worth.
    Who is this minister of consequence?
    Minister Zhao—a man of virtue unparalleled.
    With vision fixed upon the art of governance,
    He rescued the realm from its darkest hour.
    With steady hand he upheld the throne,
    Raising it to its zenith.
    His deeds shine eternal in the royal house,
    His grace flows abundantly among the people.
    Though ancient sages bore the title of great counselor,
    None could surpass what this man has wrought.
    His heart, his very countenance—
    They are the mirror of his truth.
    May he share in the kingdom's glory,
    For ten thousand years and beyond.
  footnotes:
    - Minister Zhao (趙公) refers to Zhao Jun (조준), a prominent statesman of the early Joseon dynasty and close advisor to King Taejo.
    - The image of 'hand supporting the sun's axle' (日轂) is a classical metaphor for supporting and upholding the throne and state.
    - This work is a 'zhenzan' (眞贊)—a traditional form of eulogy meant to commemorate virtuous officials.
